<br>
The second change they mentioned at fan faire which is causing issues is the hate list. Previously the hate list was capped at 60 players. One defect in that code cropped up when this hate list reached capacity - it was dropping players who were furthest away from the mob from the list completely, not the lowest aggro players as one would expect. This allowed wizards, rangers, other ranged damagers to stand further away than the rest of the raid and do a lot of damage for 0 aggro in raids larger than 60 people.<br>
<br>
I'm guessing the hate list reworking explains some people seeing wizards getting summoned as they're used to blasting at a faster rate probably.  Rangers just got a double whammy so its bound to suck. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=treage>Treage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/03 9:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Aggro and Taunt after April 8 patch</span><hr size=1> Tonight I played in Hate's Fury and also noticed that my buddy the rogue couldn't shake the aggro.<br>
