<br>
Got in a group.<br>
<br>
Taunt worked better on yellow cons for me than it had previously. Which is good.<br>
<br>
But Aggro ping ponged all night.<br>
<br>
Part of that is my level, as I was lowest in the group.<br>
<br>
BUT, I noticed that early slows (and the shammy was slowing early a LOT) only drew aggro maybe once or twice all night. AND I could taunt off of her easily.<br>
<br>
The bad news was nukes from the wizard and the druid were getting aggro pretty fierce. And since the druid was snaring as well, (and snaring early), he got aggro a lot and it was harder to get it back from him.<br>
<br>
The chanter bot that stayed outside of group would get aggro by tashing first and then nuking. It got bad once, and he died. Right after a nuke landed, that particular Virulent Arachnid had had enough with said chanter, I guess and ate him.<br>
<br>
Most of this stuff, though, I'm used to. Aggro's always a pain.<br>
<br>
The problem I had was with the two rogues.<br>
<br>
Their evades weren't as effective as usual. And even with MULTIPLE red epic procs I was occasionally having trouble getting aggro back.<br>
<br>
All in all, I had a fun night, but it was very different. The melees and casters I'm USED to being able to keep aggrom from, I was having to work like a beast to taunt off of. The casters I'm USED to getting aggro quick, spent most of the evening aggro free.<br>
<br>
Anyways, more adventuring (and of course my not so accurate brand of testing!) is needed before I can figure out what's going on. All I know is, it's kinda different out there, but frighteningly familiar territory nonetheless.<br>
